    "137113051": {
      "title": "Holographic tests on ceramic coatings on metal surfaces",
      "abstract": "Optical holographic interferometry is applied to the detection of the presence of flaws in layered composites made by ceramic coatings on metallic substrates. Tests have been carried out by utilising conventional double-exposure holography with the samples subjected to thermal stress. A qualitative analysis of the interferometric fringe pattern portrays the state of integrity of the coating. The experimental results have shown that the method is able to detect defects, such as cavities, cracks, inclusions and disbonds in ceramics with a metallic substrate."
